Effective advocacy and communication to promote increased coverage of children with zero dose and increase demand for vaccination, especially with focus on low performing and high risk districts:
1. Organize advocacy workshops at district level to ensure coordinated approach and priorities in high-districts (50) and in selected low performing villages (with village chiefs) (HR2-32, HR2-33, and HR34);
2. Provide technical assistance to Communication Task Force strengthening at national, provincial and district level (consisting of MoH, Local Council, Lao Front, Lao Women Union, Lao Youth, MoE, MoICT, Development Partners);
3. Provide technical assistance to strengthen the social mobilization network at district and community level to implement demand generation activities by mapping poor performing villages in terms of SBCC;
4. Organize community orientation meetings/training for community influencers, including village heads, religious leaders, etc with a focus on 50 high-risk districts based on the fully immunization village model concept

